  "text": "The canonical Deployment service deployment pattern in Kubernetes is distributed across the api and client-go repositories:\n\n1. **API Type Definition**: The authoritative Deployment struct is defined in api--v0.32.0/apps/v1/types.go (line 359) with the comment \"Deployment enables declarative updates for Pods and ReplicaSets.\" The struct contains TypeMeta for Kubernetes metadata, ObjectMeta for standard object metadata, Spec (DeploymentSpec) for desired behavior, and Status (DeploymentStatus) for observed status. DeploymentSpec includes Replicas count, Selector for label matching, Template for pod specification, and Strategy for update behavior (RollingUpdate or Recreate).\n\n2. **Client-side Code Pattern**: The canonical Go code example showing how to create a Deployment using the client library is in client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go. This example demonstrates the complete workflow: creating a Kubernetes clientset, creating a Deployment with appsv1.Deployment struct, using deploymentsClient.Create() to create it, implementing conflict-safe updates with retry.RetryOnConflict(), listing deployments, and deleting deployments with proper cleanup. The example uses the typed client interface and shows best practices like retry logic for concurrent updates.\n\n3. **Developer Documentation**: The deployment workflow documentation is found in multiple locations:\n   - client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md provides detailed instructions for running the typed client example, explaining the four fundamental operations (Create, List, Update, Delete) and showing expected output\n   - client-go--v0.32.0/examples/README.md categorizes examples and lists \"Managing resources with API\" as the basic deployment resource management pattern\n   - client-go--v0.32.0/examples/dynamic-create-update-delete-deployment/README.md offers an alternative pattern using the dynamic client package for loose coupling and runtime binding\n\n4. **Client Interface**: The typed client interface for Deployments is defined in client-go--v0.32.0/kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go, containing DeploymentInterface with methods for Create, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, DeleteCollection, Get, List, Watch, Patch, Apply, ApplyStatus, GetScale, UpdateScale, and ApplyScale operations. This interface enables strongly-typed, compile-time validated access to the Deployment API."
}

